review_comments.body:
nit: Can we keep the if-statement? I suppose add() on the same element multiple times would just replace the previous element in the set and end up as a no-op, but it seems clearer to me to keep the "contains" there, especially now that you've switched to a hash-based container and it would be an O(1) operation, e.g.

```
if (!writers.contains(bucketWriter)) {		
  writers.add(bucketWriter);		
}
```

