review_comments.body:
This is likely going to be flaky under system load. You could probably make it fail by running this test in a loop while also running stress -c 16 in another terminal.

I would suggest doing something like this:

```
FileUtils.deleteDirectory(baseDir);
final long TIMEOUT_MILLIS = 15000;
while (System.currentTimeMillis() < beforeCheckPointWrite + TIMEOUT_MILLIS) {
  if (channel.getChannelCounter().getCheckpointWriteErrorCount() > 0) {
    break;
  }
  Thread.sleep(10);
}
// the channel's directory has been deleted so the checkpoint write should have failed
assertThat("checkpointWriteErrorCount",
    channel.getChannelCounter().getCheckpointWriteErrorCount(),
    greaterThan(0));
```
You could probably even wrap that loop in a helper function and have it take a lambda expression, i.e.

```
void assertEventuallyTrue(String description, BooleanSupplier expr, long timeoutMillis) {
  long start = System.currentTimeMillis();
  while (System.currentTimeMillis() < start + timeoutMillis) {
    if (expr.getAsBoolean()) break;
    Thread.sleep(10); // Sleep for 10ms before each retry
  }
  assertTrue(desc, expr.getAsBoolean());
}

FileUtils.deleteDirectory(baseDir);
long timeoutMillis = 15000;
assertEventuallyTrue("checkpointWriteErrorCount > 0",
                     () -> channel.getChannelCounter().getCheckpointWriteErrorCount() > 0,
                     timeoutMillis);
```

