review_comments.body:
This sleep will make this test potentially flaky. Can you make it more reliable? Perhaps using the assertEventuallyTrue() function I suggest in another comment below. Perhaps you could put the entire following block in a lambda, i.e.

```
  assertEventuallyTrue("putErrorCount > 0",
      () -> {
        Transaction tx = channel.getTransaction();
        tx.begin();
        try {
          channel.put(EventBuilder.withBody("test".getBytes()));
          tx.commit();
          tx.close();
        } catch (ChannelException ex) {
          log.info("ChannelException", ex);
        }
        return channelCounter.getEventPutErrorCount() > 0;
      },
      timeoutMillis);
```

